radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild dependent atelectasis at the imaged lung bases; small hiatal hernia; gallbladder moderately distended; no focal lesions or biliary dilatation; normal adrenal glands, spleen, and pancreas; mild prominence of distal ileal loops with fecalization; moderate fecal loading in the right colon; normal imaged portion of the appendix and small cecal diverticula; no intra-abdominal free fluid or air; normal abdominal aorta and patent portal vein, splenic vein, and superior mesenteric vein.
